HEADWORD: Halfbeak
<hw>Half"beak`</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧f"b⟦emac⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any slender, marine fish of the genus
<gen>Hemirhamphus</gen>, or of the family <fam>Hemiramphidae</fam>,
having an elongated protruding lower jaw; -- called also
<altname>balahoo</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Half blood</ent>⟦br⟧
